OSI MODEL 
There are 7 layers of the osi model;
1. Pysical
2. Data link
3. Network
4.Transport
5. Session
6. Presentation
7. Application

Note: You don't need to memorise this layers, you just need to understand them and to do that, i'll break it down using real life scenerios or example

OSI MODEL USING A REAL-LIFE ANALOGY ( POSTAL SYSTEM)

Imagige sending a letter to someone

Layer 7 - Application
   You write your message

Layer 6 - Presentation
   You choose athe language ( English, French, Encryption)

Layer 5 - Session
   You start the converstion  ("Hello?" or Bonjour)

Layer 4 -Transport
   You arrange your message, by divifing the message into numbered pages and ensure delivery.

Layer 3 - Network
   You Write the destination Address

Layer 2 - Data Link
   You Package it in an emvelope for the local post office

Layer 1 - Physical
   It travels pysically (truck, plane or wire)


NOW REVERSE IT ON THE RECIEVER SIDE

THAT'S OSI



